
##
# CIS 3238 - Software Design Final Project
# Group: Alex Burns, Vuk Petrovic, Roman Danylyshyn, Michael Weidner
#
# Project type: Open-source contribution
# Original project: CMUS - C* Music Player
# Original Github URL: https://github.com/cmus/cmus
#
# Newly implemented features:
#
# 1. Music visualizer 
#      - Bar frequency visualizer for audio using Pulseaudio for input using frequency range 50-10KHz	
#      - Configure file for setting default options for:
#         * Sensitivity
#         * Bar width
#         * Spacing between bars
#         * Bar color
#         * Background color 		
#         * Gravity setting for bar drop rate
#       - Bars autofill terminal screen and dynamically respond to terminal resize
#       - User Controls:
#         * Up Key: Increase sensitivity by 5%
#         * Down Key: Decrease sensitivity by 5%
#         * Right Key: Increase bar width by 1
#         * Left Key: Decrease bar width by 1
#         * R Key: Reloads config
#         * B Key: Cycles through background color options
#         * C Key: Cycles through bar color options
#         * Q Key: Quit the visualizer
#        - Added falloff, smoothing, and gravity to provide smoother visualizer performance
#        - Added autosensitivity to lower bar height if sensitivity value causes bars to exceed terminal 
#
# 2. Soundcloud music downloader
#      - Download a single song, provided a URL in the form "https://soundcloud.com/<song_name>"
#      	 ex.
#		:soundcloud scdl -l https://soundcloud.com/skrillex/the-game-el-chapo
#      - Download an entire playlist provided a URL in the form of "https://soundcloud.com/<username>/sets/<playlist_name>"
#      	 ex.
#		:soundcloud scdl -l https://soundcloud.com/sets/dirty-vibe-remixes
#      - Specify default download directory for future use
#      	 ex.
#		:soundcloud default /User/John/soundcloud_downloads/
#
#	The next time you download a song, CMUS will prefer to use your default directory unless you specify a new path:
#
#	ex.
#		:soundcloud scdl -l https://soundcloud.com/skrillex/the-game-el-chapo -path /User/John/soundcloud_downloads
#
#	The -path argument will create the directory if it does not exist already.
##

